Titolo: Dragster (video game)

Anno: 1980

Descrizione: Dragster, released in 1980 for the Atari Video Computer System, is one of the first video games developed by Activision. It was programmed by David Crane, who later wrote Pitfall!. The objective of the game is to either beat the player's opponent across the screen or to race against the clock for best time, depending on the settings used. Dragster is an unauthorized adaptation of the 1977 Kee Games coin-op Drag Race.

Genere: Drag racing 

Valutazione: N/A
